  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Let $A=\\{a_1<\\cdots<a_k\\}$ be a finite set of positive integers and extend it to an infinite sequence $\\overline{A}=\\{a_1<a_2<\\cdots \\}$ by defining $a_{n+1}$ for $n\\geq k$ to be the least integer exceeding $a_n$ which is not of the form $a_i+a_j$ with $i,j\\leq n$. Is it true that the sequence of differences $a_{m+1}-a_m$ is eventually periodic?",
